esource/London\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"ourPrivacy notice Adam Peatysaid\", \"from\": 327, \"to\": 359}, {\"ngram\": \"a new relaxed mindset\", \"from\": 360, \"to\": 381}, {\"ngram\": \"passage\", \"from\": 416, \"to\": 423}, {\"ngram\": \"this summer's ParisOlympicsby\", \"from\": 427, \"to\": 456}, {\"ngram\": \"his signature\", \"from\": 476, \"to\": 489}, {\"ngram\": \"breaststroke event\", \"from\": 495, \"to\": 513}, {\"ngram\": \"the first day\", \"from\": 517, \"to\": 530}, {\"ngram\": \"the British Championships\", \"from\": 534, \"to\": 559}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 29-year-old touched the wall in 57.94 seconds in the evening's final - the fastest men's 100m breaststroke time in the world this year and an improvement on the 59.10 seconds it took him to win bronze at February's World Championships in Doha.\", \"from\": 573, \"to\": 820, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 815, \"end\": 819, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Doha\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.978448011311691e-14, \"text\": \"Doha\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Doha\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Doha\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the wall\", \"from\": 597, \"to\": 605}, {\"ngram\": \"57.94 seconds\", \"from\": 609, \"to\": 622}, {\"ngram\": \"breaststroke time\", \"from\": 671, \"to\": 688}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 692, \"to\": 701}, {\"ngram\": \"an improvement\", \"from\": 716, \"to\": 730}, {\"ngram\": \"the 59.10 seconds\", \"from\": 734, \"to\": 751}, {\"ngram\": \"bronze\", \"from\": 771, \"to\": 777}, {\"ngram\": \"February's World Championships\", \"from\": 781, \"to\": 811}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Peaty, who still holds the world record of 56.88 seconds in the event, is now set to defend his back-to-back Olympic titles after securing a nomination in the British championships, one year after pulling out of the 2023 event to begin what became an extended mental health-motivated hiatus from the sport.\", \"from\": 822, \"to\": 1128, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 981, \"end\": 1002, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UK_Athletics\", \"score\": 0.999999999998181, \"rank\": 1.8095663676474184e-12, \"text\": \"British championships\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UK_Athletics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UK_Athletics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Peaty\", \"from\": 822, \"to\": 827}, {\"ngram\": \"the world record\", \"from\": 845, \"to\": 861}, {\"ngram\": \"56.88 seconds\", \"from\": 865, \"to\": 878}, {\"ngram\": \"the event\", \"from\": 882, \"to\": 891}, {\"ngram\": \"back\", \"from\": 926, \"to\": 930}, {\"ngram\": \"a nomination\", \"from\": 961, \"to\": 973}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2023 event\", \"from\": 1034, \"to\": 1048}, {\"ngram\": \"an extended mental health-motivated hiatus\", \"from\": 1070, \"to\": 1112}, {\"ngram\": \"the sport\", \"from\": 1118, \"to\": 1127}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Peaty said afterwards: \\\"I am not fully back, I have still got a second!\", \"from\": 1130, \"to\": 1201, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Peaty\", \"from\": 1130, \"to\": 1135}, {\"ngram\": \"a second\", \"from\": 1192, \"to\": 1200}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's always going to be my mindset, but I have got a healthy approach to it.\", \"from\": 1203, \"to\": 1280, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"my mindset\", \"from\": 1228, \"to\": 1238}, {\"ngram\": \"a healthy approach\", \"from\": 1255, \"to\": 1273}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A few years ago, I'd have come out of there disappointed.\", \"from\": 1281, \"to\": 1338, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I have learned to appreciate the moments of greatness for myself.\", \"from\": 1340, \"to\": 1406, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the moments\", \"from\": 1370, \"to\": 1381}, {\"ngram\": \"greatness\", \"from\": 1385, \"to\": 1394}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For me, that was a great swim, executed well - but the most promising thing is that I am finding peace in the water now, instead of anger and just fighting it, and trying to win like that.\", \"from\": 1407, \"to\": 1595, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a great swim\", \"from\": 1424, \"to\": 1436}, {\"ngram\": \"the most promising thing\", \"from\": 1458, \"to\": 1482}, {\"ngram\": \"peace\", \"from\": 1504, \"to\": 1509}, {\"ngram\": \"the water\", \"from\": 1513, \"to\": 1522}, {\"ngram\": \"anger\", \"from\": 1539, \"to\": 1544}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am finding a new version of myself which I am really liking, and I think that's a version that can do really well at the Olympics.\\\"\", \"from\": 1597, \"to\": 1731, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a new version\", \"from\": 1611, \"to\": 1624}, {\"ngram\": \"a version\", \"from\": 1680, \"to\": 1689}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 1717, \"to\": 1729}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The most direct way of securing aParis 2024nomination this week is to finish first in the open finals of each individual event, provided athletes clock in at or under a specific time set by the newly-rebranded Aquatics GB, though nominations are still subject to an official rubber-stamp by the British Olympic Association.\", \"from\": 1733, \"to\": 2056, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1952, \"end\": 1954, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.9987225906981814, \"rank\": 0.0012664581674770644, \"text\": \"GB\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}, {\"begin\": 2028, \"end\": 2055, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Olympic_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"British Olympic Association\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Olympic_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Olympic_Association\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The most direct way\", \"from\": 1733, \"to\": 1752}, {\"ngram\": \"aParis 2024nomination\", \"from\": 1765, \"to\": 1786}, {\"ngram\": \"the open finals\", \"from\": 1819, \"to\": 1834}, {\"ngram\": \"each individual event\", \"from\": 1838, \"to\": 1859}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes clock\", \"from\": 1870, \"to\": 1884}, {\"ngram\": \"a specific time\", \"from\": 1900, \"to\": 1915}, {\"ngram\": \"nominations\", \"from\": 1963, \"to\": 1974}, {\"ngram\": \"an official rubber-stamp\", \"from\": 1996, \"to\": 2020}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Peaty emerged from his afternoon heat with a time of 58.53, the only man of 64 entrants in the event's heats to touch the wall in under a minute, marking another significant step on a comeback journey for the five-time Olympic medallist.\", \"from\": 2058, \"to\": 2295, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Peaty\", \"from\": 2058, \"to\": 2063}, {\"ngram\": \"his afternoon heat\", \"from\": 2077, \"to\": 2095}, {\"ngram\": \"a time\", \"from\": 2101, \"to\": 2107}, {\"ngram\": \"the only man\", \"from\": 2118, \"to\": 2130}, {\"ngram\": \"64 entrants\", \"from\": 2134, \"to\": 2145}, {\"ngram\": \"the event's heats\", \"from\": 2149, \"to\": 2166}, {\"ngram\": \"the wall\", \"from\": 2176, \"to\": 2184}, {\"ngram\": \"a minute\", \"from\": 2194, \"to\": 2202}, {\"ngram\": \"another significant step\", \"from\": 2212, \"to\": 2236}, {\"ngram\": \"a comeback journey\", \"from\": 2240, \"to\": 2258}, {\"ngram\": \"the five-time Olympic medallist\", \"from\": 2263, \"to\": 2294}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He was sidelined from the 2022 World Championships due to a foot injury and last year withdrew from the British Championships, making his competitive return in Doha.\", \"from\": 2297, \"to\": 2462, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2401, \"end\": 2422, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UK_Athletics\", \"score\": 0.999999999998181, \"rank\": 1.8095663676474184e-12, \"text\": \"British Championships\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UK_Athletics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UK_Athletics\"}, {\"begin\": 2457, \"end\": 2461, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Doha\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.978448011311691e-14, \"text\": \"Doha\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Doha\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Doha\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the 2022 World Championships\", \"from\": 2319, \"to\": 2347}, {\"ngram\": \"a foot injury\", \"from\": 2355, \"to\": 2368}, {\"ngram\": \"his competitive return\", \"from\": 2431, \"to\": 2453}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"This is a real win for my team, my family and myself,\\\" said Peaty.\", \"from\": 2464, \"to\": 2531, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a real win\", \"from\": 2473, \"to\": 2483}, {\"ngram\": \"my team\", \"from\": 2488, \"to\": 2495}, {\"ngram\": \"my family\", \"from\": 2497, \"to\": 2506}, {\"ngram\": \"Peaty\", \"from\": 2525, \"to\": 2530}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We have come through the past three years of hell.\", \"from\": 2532, \"to\": 2583, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the past three years\", \"from\": 2554, \"to\": 2574}, {\"ngram\": \"hell\", \"from\": 2578, \"to\": 2582}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I did not want to see a pool again.\", \"from\": 2585, \"to\": 2621, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a pool\", \"from\": 2608, \"to\": 2614}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The sport had broken me.\", \"from\": 2622, \"to\": 2646, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The sport\", \"from\": 2622, \"to\": 2631}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I did not know what route to go down and so many things got in my way.\", \"from\": 2647, \"to\": 2717, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"what route\", \"from\": 2662, \"to\": 2672}, {\"ngram\": \"so many things\", \"from\": 2688, \"to\": 2702}, {\"ngram\": \"my way\", \"from\": 2710, \"to\": 2716}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But now I am waking up each day and enjoying my job.\", \"from\": 2718, \"to\": 2770, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"my job\", \"from\": 2763, \"to\": 2769}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Who knows what the ending is going to be but I am having fun along the way.\\\"\", \"from\": 2771, \"to\": 2847, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the ending\", \"from\": 2786, \"to\": 2796}, {\"ngram\": \"fun\", \"from\": 2828, \"to\": 2831}, {\"ngram\": \"the way\", \"from\": 2838, \"to\": 2845}]}, {\"sentence\": \"James Wilby, who finished second to Peaty, missed the 59.45sec nomination time by an agonising 0.02 seconds but could still be one of a maximum 30 swimmers nominated by Aquatics GB following the championships' conclusion on Sunday.\", \"from\": 2849, \"to\": 3080, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2849, \"end\": 2860, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Wilby\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.0476956835428415e-15, \"text\": \"James Wilby\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Wilby\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Wilby\"}, {\"begin\": 3027, \"end\": 3029, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.9987225906981814, \"rank\": 0.0012664581674770644, \"text\": \"GB\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Peaty\", \"from\": 2885, \"to\": 2890}, {\"ngram\": \"the 59.45sec nomination time\", \"from\": 2899, \"to\": 2927}, {\"ngram\": \"an agonising 0.02 seconds\", \"from\": 2931, \"to\": 2956}, {\"ngram\": \"a maximum 30 swimmers\", \"from\": 2983, \"to\": 3004}, {\"ngram\": \"the championships' conclusion\", \"from\": 3040, \"to\": 3069}, {\"ngram\": \"Sunday\", \"from\": 3073, \"to\": 3079}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Scotland's Keanna MacInnes, 22, punched her ticket after overtaking Laura Stephens 